# AppForge by OYARO 🚀

**No-code Android App Builder - Create Native Apps Without Coding**

AppForge by OYARO is an offline-first mobile application that allows anyone to create real, installable Android apps using plain English descriptions. No coding required, no internet needed after setup.

## ✨ Key Features

### 🎯 Core Capabilities
- **Natural Language App Generation** - Describe your app idea in plain English, AI generates the code
- **Real Native APKs** - Builds genuine, installable Android apps that appear in your launcher
- **Mostly Offline** - Only AI code generation needs internet; everything else runs locally
- **60+ Pre-built Demos** - Sample apps showcasing native Android features
- **Instant Prototyping** - Perfect for quick tools, games, dashboards, and utilities

### 📱 Hardware Access

**37+ Native Bridges** including:
- 📷 Camera (photo & video)
- 📍 GPS and Location Services
- 🎵 Audio (playback & recording)
- 🔔 Notifications
- 📱 SMS & Phone Calls
- 📧 Contacts & Calendar
- 🌐 WiFi & Bluetooth
- 💾 File Storage
- 🎮 Sensors (accelerometer, gyroscope, etc.)
- 🏷️ NFC Tags
- And 25+ more features...

### 🤖 AI Integration

Supports multiple AI providers:
- Anthropic Claude
- OpenAI GPT-4
- Google Gemini
- OpenRouter
- Local LLMs

### 💾 Offline Features
- App generation happens on your device
- No cloud storage required
- All apps stored locally
- Complete privacy

## 📥 Download & Install

### Current Version: v1.0.0

**Download AppForge by OYARO APK:**

📱 [Download Latest Release](https://github.com/emmanueloyaro123-jpg/appforge-oyaro/releases)

**Installation Steps:**
1. Enable "Install from Unknown Sources" in Settings → Security
2. Download the APK from releases
3. Open and tap "Install"
4. Launch AppForge
5. Grant requested permissions
6. Start creating apps!

## 🔧 Build From Source

### Prerequisites
- Java 11 or higher
- Android SDK (API 31+)
- Flutter 3.13.0+
- Gradle 7.0+
- 10GB free disk space

### Quick Build

```bash
# Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/emmanueloyaro123-jpg/appforge-oyaro.git
cd appforge-oyaro

# Make build script executable
chmod +x build.sh

# Run the build
./build.sh

# Output: bin/AppForge-by-OYARO.apk
